==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Privateer
<hw>Pri`va*teer"</hw> <pr>(pr⟦imac⟧`v⟦adot⟧*t⟦emac⟧r")</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Private</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
armed private vessel which bears the commission of the sovereign power
to cruise against the enemy. See <cref>Letters of marque</cref>, under
<er>Marque</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The commander of a privateer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Kidd soon threw off the character of a <qex>privateer</qex> and
became a pirate.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Privateer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Privateer
<hw>Pri`va*teer"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Privateered</conjf> <pr>(pr⟦imac⟧`v⟦adot⟧*t⟦emac⟧rd")</pr>;
<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Privateering</conjf>.]</vmorph>
<def>To cruise in a privateer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Privateering</ent>⟦br⟧
